  "prompt": "What is if statement?",
  "response": "An if statement is a fundamental control structure in programming that allows you to make decisions and execute different code blocks based on specific conditions. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n1. Basic Syntax (in most programming languages):\n```\nif (condition) {\n    // Code to execute if condition is true\n}\n```\n\n2. Simple Example (in multiple languages):\nPython:\n```python\nx = 10\nif x > 5:\n    print(\"x is greater than 5\")\n```\n\nJavaScript:\n```javascript\nlet x = 10;\nif (x > 5) {\n    console.log(\"x is greater than 5\");\n}\n```\n\nJava:\n```java\nint x = 10;\nif (x > 5) {\n    System.out.println(\"x is greater than 5\");\n}\n```\n\n3. Extended Versions:\na. If-Else:\n```python\nif condition:\n    # Code if true\nelse:\n    # Code if false\n```\n\nb. If-Elif-Else (Else If):\n```python\nif condition1:\n    # Code if condition1 is true\nelif condition2:\n    # Code if condition2 is true\nelse:\n    # Code if no conditions are true\n```\n\n4. Nested If Statements:\n```python\nif outer_condition:\n    if inner_condition:\n        # Code for nested condition\n```\n\n5. Comparison Operators:\n- == (equal to)\n- != (not equal to)\n- > (greater than)\n- < (less than)\n- >= (greater than or equal to)\n- <= (less than or equal to)\n\n6. Logical Operators:\n- and (both conditions must be true)\n- or (at least one condition must be true)\n- not (negates the condition)\n\nKey Points:\n- Used for decision-making\n- Executes code based on boolean conditions\n- Can have multiple branches\n- Essential for controlling program flow",
